11	3	text-structure-1	Section 1: Understanding the Question Format		Before diving into strategies for answering Text Structure questions, it's crucial to understand their structure and format. By recognizing the key components and elements, you'll be better equipped to approach them effectively.\r\n\r\nText Structure questions on the Digital SAT typically follow this format:\r\n\r\n- A passage or paragraph is provided.\r\n- A specific sentence or portion of the text is underlined or highlighted.\r\n- The question then asks about the function or purpose of the underlined or highlighted portion within the text.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n- "Which choice best describes the function of the underlined sentence in the text as a whole?"\r\n- "Which choice best states the function of the highlighted portion in the overall structure of the text?"\r\n\r\nBelow the question, you'll find a list of four answer choices, each offering a different explanation of the function or purpose of the specified text portion. Your task is to select the option that most accurately describes its role within the passage.	\N
