e following best expresses the main idea of this passage?\r\n\r\nA) The printing press was invented in the 15th century. \r\nB) The printing press made books more affordable and accessible. \r\nC) The printing press had a revolutionary impact on the spread of information and knowledge, shaping historical events. \r\nD) Modern digital technology is more revolutionary than the printing press.\r\n\r\nExplanation: \r\nThe correct answer is C. \r\nThis question helps illustrate common pitfalls:\r\n1.\tFocusing on Specific Details: Option A is a factual detail from the passage, not the main idea.\r\n2.\tSelecting an Answer That's Too Narrow: Option B captures one effect of the printing press but doesn't encompass its broader impact.\r\n3.\tBeing Misled by Strong Language: Option D might be tempting due to the comparison made in the last sentence, but it overstates what the passage actually says and ignores much of the content about the printing press.\r\n4.\tIgnoring Parts of the Passage: Option C is the only choice that accounts for the entire passage, including the historical impact and the comparison to modern technology.\r\n\r\nOption C avoids these pitfalls by capturing the overall message about the revolutionary impact of the printing press on the spread of information and its historical significance, while also alluding to the comparison with modern technology.	\N
