ixed and debates continue about its feasibility and long-term effects. As technological advancements continue to reshape the job market, the discussion around UBI is likely to intensify."\r\n\r\nA) Universal basic income is the best solution to economic inequality.\r\nB) Universal basic income is too expensive to implement on a large scale.\r\nC) Universal basic income is a debated concept with potential benefits and challenges, gaining relevance due to economic changes.\r\nD) Experiments with universal basic income have proven its effectiveness.\r\n\r\nCorrect Answer: C\r\n\r\nDetailed explanation:\r\n\r\nA) Incorrect: The passage presents UBI as a potential solution, not definitively the best one. It also discusses both arguments for and against UBI, not just its benefits.\r\n\r\nB) Incorrect: While the passage mentions cost as a concern raised by critics, it doesn't conclude that UBI is too expensive to implement. The passage presents a more balanced view of the debate.\r\n\r\nC) Correct: This option accurately captures the main idea by acknowledging UBI as a debated concept, mentioning both potential benefits and challenges, and noting its relevance in the context of economic changes (like job displacement due to automation).\r\n\r\nD) Incorrect: The passage states that results from UBI experiments have been mixed, not that they have proven its effectiveness.\r\n\r\nQuestion 7:\r\nRead the following passage and identify the main idea:\r\n\r\n"The field of genetic engineering has made significant strides in recent years, offering potential solutions to various global challenges. In agriculture, genetically modified crops have been developed to resist pests, tolerate drought, and increase nutritional value, potentially addressing food security issues. In medicine, gene therapy shows promise for treating genetic disorders and certain types of cancer. However, these advancements also raise ethical concerns, including questions about the long-term effects of genetica