ns the peace and tranquility found in nature but does not provide specific evidence or studies to support the claim that spending time in natural environments improves mental health.\r\n\r\n**B)** **Correct Answer**. This quotation directly supports the claim by citing studies that show a reduction in stress and anxiety, providing concrete evidence of the mental health benefits of spending time in nature.\r\n\r\n**C)** This choice discusses the inspirational beauty of nature and the resulting inner calm, but it lacks specific evidence or data to directly support the claim about mental health improvement.\r\n\r\n**D)** This choice highlights the engaging activities available in nature, but it does not directly connect these activities to mental health improvements with concrete evidence.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Practice Question 2\r\n\r\n"The Role of Literature" is a 2022 article by Maria Lopez. In the article, Lopez claims that literature plays a crucial role in shaping cultural identity. Which quotation from "The Role of Literature" most effectively illustrates this claim?\r\n\r\n**A)** "Many readers find themselves reflected in the stories they read, gaining a deeper understanding of their own lives."\r\n\r\n**B)** "Literary works from different periods offer unique insights into the values and norms of their respective times."\r\n\r\n**C)** "Through the characters and narratives in literature, individuals can explore and connect with the cultural heritage of their society."\r\n\r\n**D)** "The impact of a novel can extend beyond entertainment, fostering empathy and a sense of belonging among its readers."\r\n\r\n**Correct Answer:** C\r\n\r\n**Explanation of Answer Choices:**\r\n\r\n**A)** This choice talks about personal reflection and understanding gained from literature, but it does not specifically address how literature shapes cultural identity.\r\n\r\n**B)** This choice discusses the insights into values and norms provided by literature but does not directly co