xplanation: Dashes are correctly used to set off the non-essential list of ingredients.\r\nQuestion 5\r\nThe committee's decision was unexpected__ they chose to postpone the event until next year.\r\nA) NO CHANGE\r\nB) unexpected: they chose\r\nC) unexpected, they chose\r\nD) unexpected; they chose\r\nCorrect Answer: B\r\nExplanation: A colon is used to introduce the explanation of the committee's decision.\r\nQuestion 6\r\nThe new exhibit at the museum showcases modern art__ paintings, sculptures, and digital installations.\r\nA) NO CHANGE\r\nB) art, paintings, sculptures, and digital installations.\r\nC) art; paintings, sculptures, and digital installations.\r\nD) art: paintings, sculptures, and digital installations.\r\nCorrect Answer: D\r\nExplanation: A colon is used to introduce the list of items in the exhibit.\r\nQuestion 7\r\nThe recipe calls for three main ingredients__ flour, sugar, and butter__ to make the cake.\r\nA) NO CHANGE\r\nB) ingredients; flour, sugar, and butter,\r\nC) ingredients: flour, sugar, and butter,\r\nD) ingredients flour, sugar, and butter,\r\nCorrect Answer: A\r\nExplanation: Dashes are used to set off the non-essential list of ingredients.\r\nQuestion 8\r\nThe reason for his absence was clear__ he had to attend an urgent meeting.\r\nA) NO CHANGE\r\nB) clear: he had to\r\nC) clear, he had to\r\nD) clear he had to\r\nCorrect Answer: B\r\nExplanation: A colon is used to introduce the explanation for his absence.\r\nQuestion 9\r\nThe conference will cover various topics__ technology, healthcare, and education.\r\nA) NO CHANGE\r\nB) topics: technology, healthcare, and education.\r\nC) topics; technology, healthcare, and education.\r\nD) topics, technology, healthcare, and education.\r\nCorrect Answer: B\r\nExplanation: A colon is used to introduce the list of topics covered in the conference.\r\nQuestion 10\r\nHer explanation was concise__ she summarized the entire project in just a few sentences.\r\nA) NO CHANGE\r\nB) concise: she summar