74	14	parallel-structure	Parallel Structure		Parallel structure (also known as parallelism) involves using the same pattern of words to show that two or more ideas have the same level of importance. It makes sentences clearer and more effective.\r\nLists and Parallel Structure\r\nWhen listing items in a sentence, ensure each item follows the same grammatical structure.\r\nExample:\r\nIncorrect: She enjoys reading books, to write stories, and painting.\r\nCorrect: She enjoys reading books, writing stories, and painting.\r\nIn the correct sentence, all items in the list are gerunds (reading, writing, painting).\r\n \r\nConjunctions and Parallel Structure\r\nWhen joining two or more items with conjunctions like "and," "or," and "but," ensure each item has the same structure.\r\nExample:\r\nIncorrect: He wanted to improve his fitness by running daily and to eat healthier.\r\nCorrect: He wanted to improve his fitness by running daily and eating healthier.\r\nThe correct sentence uses gerunds (running, eating) after the preposition "by."\r\n \r\nTwo-Part Parallel Structure\r\nSome parallel structure questions involve word pairs. Identifying these pairs helps in maintaining parallelism.\r\nExample:\r\nIncorrect: She is not only talented but also has a great work ethic.\r\nCorrect: She is not only talented but also hardworking.\r\nBoth parts of the sentence now have adjectives (talented, hardworking).\r\n \r\nParallel Structure in Comparisons\r\nComparative structures should also maintain parallelism.\r\nExample:\r\nIncorrect: Running is better than to swim.\r\nCorrect: Running is better than swimming.\r\nBoth items in the comparison are now gerunds (running, swimming).\r\n \r\nMultiple Sentences and Parallel Structure\r\nParallel structure can extend across multiple sentences. Maintaining this structure ensures clarity and balance in writing.\r\nExample:\r\nIncorrect: The teacher lectured for an hour. Then, the students were completing the assignment. Finally, they turn in their work.\r\nCorrect: The teacher lectured for an hour. The students completed the assignment. Finally, they turned in their work.\r\nEach sentence now follows a subject-verb-object structure.\r\n \r\nExercise: Parallel Structure\r\nRewrite the following sentences to maintain parallel structure:\r\n1.\tShe likes to jog, swimming, and biking.\r\nCorrect: She likes jogging, swimming, and biking.\r\n2.\tThe project involves researching the topic, writing a report, and to present findings.\r\nCorrect: The project involves researching the topic, writing a report, and presenting findings.\r\n3.\tHe is either going to the library or studies at home.\r\nCorrect: He is either going to the library or studying at home.\r\n4.\tThe coach encouraged the players to practice regularly and that they should eat healthy.\r\nCorrect: The coach encouraged the players to practice regularly and to eat healthy.\r\nBy maintaining parallel structure in writing, we ensure that our sentences are clear, concise, and easy to read.\r\nPractice Question 1:\r\nJennifer is known for her dedication to community service. Every weekend, she spends her time volunteering at local shelters, tutoring underprivileged children, and to organize neighborhood cleanups. Her efforts have not only improved the lives of many people but also inspires others to get involved in community activities.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to organize to organizing\r\nB) Change inspires to inspire\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 2:\r\nDuring the summer break, Alex decided to take on several projects. He started by painting his room, building a new bookshelf, and to plant a garden. Despite the heat, he managed to finish all his projects, and he felt a great sense of accomplishment and was proud of his hard work.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to plant to planting\r\nB) Change was proud to proud\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 3:\r\nIn preparation for the marathon, Maria followed a strict regimen. She focused on running daily, eating a balanced diet, and to get adequate sleep. Additionally, she made sure to stretch before and after her workouts, hydrate regularly, and avoiding junk food.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to get to getting\r\nB) Change avoiding to avoid\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 4:\r\nThe company’s new policy aims to improve employee satisfaction. They have introduced flexible working hours, enhanced healthcare benefits, and to provide opportunities for professional development. These changes are designed to attract top talent, reduce turnover rates, and increasing overall productivity.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to provide to providing\r\nB) Change increasing to increase\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 5:\r\nThe environmental campaign focused on three main goals: reducing plastic waste, conserving water, and to promote renewable energy sources. Through various initiatives, the organization aimed to educate the public, influence policy changes, and encouraging sustainable practices.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to promote to promoting\r\nB) Change encouraging to encourage\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 1:\r\nAt the annual tech conference, speakers focused on various topics including artificial intelligence, blockchain technology, and to improve cybersecurity measures. The event aimed to bring together industry leaders, foster innovation, and networking among professionals.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to improve to improving\r\nB) Change networking to network\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 2:\r\nIn her spare time, Sarah enjoys painting landscapes, playing the piano, and to read historical novels. She finds these activities relaxing, intellectually stimulating, and brings her a great deal of satisfaction.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to read to reading\r\nB) Change brings to bring\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 3:\r\nThe city's new urban development plan includes expanding public transportation, creating more green spaces, and to build affordable housing units. These initiatives are expected to reduce traffic congestion, enhance the quality of life, and attracting new businesses to the area.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to build to building\r\nB) Change attracting to attract\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 4:\r\nDuring the hiking trip, participants were advised to stay on marked trails, carry sufficient water, and to wear appropriate footwear. The guides emphasized the importance of safety, respecting wildlife, and leave no trace behind.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to improve the parallel structure of the sentence?\r\nA) Change to wear to wearing\r\nB) Change leave to leaving\r\nC) Both A and B\r\nD) No change needed\r\n \r\nPractice Question 5:\r\nThe university's curriculum for the environmental science program includes studying climate change, analyzing pollution data, and to develop sustainable practices. The goal is to equip students with the knowledge, skills, and prepared them for future challenges in the field.\r\nWhich of the following changes should be made to