ucture.\r\nConclusion:\r\nD) and changing forever is the most suitable choice because it maintains the grammatical parallel structure and clearly links the achievement of the Wright brothers to its lasting impact on transportation and human mobility.\r\n\r\nTherefore, the sentence should read: "This historic achievement marked the beginning of the modern aviation era and changing forever the course of transportation and human mobility."
