ion.\r\n\r\nTherefore, the sentence should read: "Leonardo da Vinci, primarily celebrated for his masterpieces like the Mona Lisa, was not just a painter but also a dedicated scientist. He enjoyed the study of anatomy, leading him to create detailed sketches of the human body and propose early concepts of human biology."
